ideDeck 3\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Image slider\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Pinterest\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"slidedeck3\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:6;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:34:\"https://www.slidedeck.com/?p=18954\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:591:\"<p>Showcasing images from any Pinterest account was never so easy. SlideDeck3 gives you the ability to create a&#160;dynamic Pinterest slider in WordPress in just 30 seconds. Also, enables&#160;you to allow visitors to pin your slider’s images to Pinterest with the click of a button. In this walkthrough, we will guide...</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/create-pinterest-slider-wordpress/\">How to create a Pinterest slider in WordPress?</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.slidedeck.com\">Responsive WordPress Slider Plugin</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Nishtha Dosaj\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4891:\"<p>Showcasing images from any Pinterest account was never so easy. SlideDeck3 gives you the ability to create a&nbsp;dynamic Pinterest slider in WordPress in just 30 seconds. Also, enables&nbsp;you to allow visitors to pin your slider’s images to Pinterest with the click of a button.</p>\n<p>In this walkthrough, we will guide you on how to make a Pinterest <a href=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/\">WordPress slider</a> using SlideDeck3.</p>\n<h2>Creating a Pinterest slider inWordPress:-</h2>\n<h4>Step ONE: &#8211; Install and Activate the SlideDeck3</h4>\n<p>First, you need to install and&nbsp;activate the <a href=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/\">SlideDeck3</a> Plugin.</p>\n<h4>Step TWO: &#8211; Creating a WordPress Post Slider</h4>\n<p>To create a WordPress Post Slider. &nbsp;Go to <strong>SlideDeck » Manage » Create SlideDeck under </strong>Dynamic Source <strong>» Select Pinterest. </strong>Give a name to the slider. Save your slider as a draft or publish it.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-18956 size-full\" src=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/dynamic-source-pin.png\" alt=\"Pinterest slider\" width=\"557\" height=\"583\" srcset=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/dynamic-source-pin.png 557w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/dynamic-source-pin-554x580.png 554w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 557px) 100vw, 557px\" /></a></p>\n<h4>Step THREE: &#8211; Configure your Pinterest source</h4>\n<p>To configure your Pinterest source, click on the Pinterest button and simply paste the URL of a user’s profile page.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-18957 size-full\" src=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/pinterest-settings.png\" alt=\"Pinterest settings\" width=\"441\" height=\"274\"/></a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h4>Step FOUR: &#8211; Publish WordPress Pinterest Slider to Your Website</h4>\n<p>You’re almost done. Next, you will need to&nbsp;<strong>Publish&nbsp;</strong>or&nbsp;<strong>Update</strong>&nbsp;your slider to a post/page. Select any of these methods to publish your slider.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-18928 size-full\" src=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/publish-methods.png\" alt=\"Publish methods - SlideDeck3\" width=\"466\" height=\"486\"/></a></p>\n<p>Finally, visit the page/post to see your WordPress post slider in action. You just made a <a href=\"http://www.slidedeck.com/docs/#pinterest\" target=\"_blank\">Pinterest WordPress image slider</a> by using SlideDeck3!</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><div class=\"slidedeck-link\"><a href=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/create-pinterest-slider-wordpress/#SlideDeck-18960\">Pinterest Demo <small>[see the SlideDeck]</small></a></div></strong></p>\n<p>Hope this tutorial helped you to create a Pinterest image slider on your WordPress site. If you have any queries or feedback, please let us know in the comments.</p>\n<p>Check out this blog if you are looking to create a <a href=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/create-wordpress-instagram-slider/\">WordPress Instagram slider</a>.</p>\n<p>For any queries or feedback, please let us know in the comments.</p>\n<br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.slidedeck.com/pricing/?utm_source=feed_ad&utm_medium=banner&utm_campaign=sd_blog\"><img src=\"//s3.amazonaws.com/assets-slidedeck2/wp-content/themes/slidedeck2/images/sd-rss.jpg\" alt=\"Easily create AWESOME WordPress sliders - Get SlideDeck\" style=\"display:block;border:none;\"/></a><p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/create-pinterest-slider-wordpress/\">How to create a Pinterest slider in WordPress?</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.slidedeck.com\">Responsive WordPress Slider Plugin</a>.</p>\n<div class=\"feedflare\">\n<a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a=s8AnnquPwWE:r_WhlBqaWro:yIl2AUoC8zA\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?d=yIl2AUoC8zA\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a=s8AnnquPwWE:r_WhlBqaWro:gIN9vFwOqvQ\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?i=s8AnnquPwWE:r_WhlBqaWro:gIN9vFwOqvQ\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a=s8AnnquPwWE:r_WhlBqaWro:V_sGLiPBpWU\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?i=s8AnnquPwWE:r_WhlBqaWro:V_sGLiPBpWU\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a=s8AnnquPwWE:r_WhlBqaWro:qj6IDK7rITs\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?d=qj6IDK7rITs\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a=s8AnnquPwWE:r_WhlBqaWro:F7zBnMyn0Lo\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?i=s8AnnquPwWE:r_WhlBqaWro:F7zBnMyn0Lo\" border=\"0\"></img></a>\n</div><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/Slidedeck/~4/s8AnnquPwWE\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:65:\"https://www.slidedeck.com/create-pinterest-slider-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"https://www.slidedeck.com/create-pinterest-slider-wordpress/\";s:7:\"attribs\"