idedeck3\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Slider\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:34:\"https://www.slidedeck.com/?p=19186\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:601:\"<p>Do you want to quickly create image/video/text/HTML slides in WordPress? SlideDeck3 allow you to mix a variety of slide types into a single presentation such as photos, videos, text and HTML documents to create a mixed content slider. Slidedeck3 plugin&#8217;s custom content feature allows you to create a responsive WordPress...</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/mixed-content-slider-wordpress/\">How to create a Mixed Content Slider in WordPress?</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.slidedeck.com\">Responsive WordPress Slider Plugin</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Nishtha Dosaj\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9877:\"<p>Do you want to quickly create image/video/text/HTML slides in WordPress? SlideDeck3 allow you to mix a variety of slide types into a single presentation such as photos, videos, text and HTML documents to create a mixed content slider.</p>\n<p>Slidedeck3 plugin&#8217;s custom content feature allows you to create a responsive <a href=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/\" target=\"_blank\">WordPress slider</a> based on your website’s content.</p>\n<p>In this article, we will guide you on how to create a mixed content slider with photos, text, video and HTML using <a href=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/\">SlideDeck3</a>. So, let&#8217;s begin.</p>\n<h2>Creating a mixed content slider in WordPress:-</h2>\n<h4>STEP One: Installation</h4>\n<p>First, you need to install and&nbsp;activate the SlideDeck3 Plugin</p>\n<h4>STEP Two: Create Slider</h4>\n<p>Upon activation, you need to Visit <strong>SlideDeck3 » Manage</strong>&nbsp;<strong>»</strong> <strong>Create <a href=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/\">SlideDeck </a></strong>under<strong> Custom Content</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-19154 size-full\" src=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Custom-content.png\" alt=\"Custom content\" width=\"411\" height=\"145\"/></a></p>\n<p><strong>Give a name to your slider and select any slide type as you require in your slider.<br />\n</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-19193 size-full\" src=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Name1.png\" alt=\"Mixed content slider\" width=\"555\" height=\"304\"/></a></p>\n<p>It’s time to add some slides. Let&#8217;s go one by one.</p>\n<p><strong>Image Slide</strong> <strong>&#8211;</strong> Click <strong>Image Slide</strong> button, a lightbox will appear where you can upload images and make settings for that particular image slide.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-19202 size-large\" src=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/upload-image-556x580.png\" alt=\"Mixed content slider\" width=\"556\" height=\"580\" srcset=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/upload-image-556x580.png 556w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/upload-image.png 594w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 556px) 100vw, 556px\" /></a></p>\n<p>There are three options available to add images. You can choose to upload images from your computer&nbsp;or select images you’ve already uploaded in Media Library of your WordPress site, or you can simply specify the URL of the image.</p>\n<p>Great, now that you’ve selected an image, select the <strong><em>Upload</em></strong> button to add these images to your slide. Once done, click <strong>Apply</strong>.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-19203 size-large\" src=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/upload-580x180.png\" alt=\"Upload image - SlideDeck3\" width=\"580\" height=\"180\" srcset=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/upload-580x180.png 580w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/upload.png 589w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 580px) 100vw, 580px\" /></a></p>\n<p>You’ll immediately see the images you added/selected appear in the <strong><em>Slide.</em></strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-19205 size-large\" src=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/image-slide-580x356.png\" alt=\"Image slider\" width=\"580\" height=\"356\" srcset=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/image-slide-580x356.png 580w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/image-slide-768x471.png 768w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/image-slide.png 818w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 580px) 100vw, 580px\" /></a></p>\n<p><strong>Text Slide &#8211; </strong>It&#8217;s time to add the next slide. Click <strong>Add Slide</strong> Button and choose <strong>Text Slide, </strong>a lightbox will appear where you can add the text you want to show into the slide.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-19207 size-large\" src=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/textslide-475x580.png\" alt=\"Text slider\" width=\"475\" height=\"580\" srcset=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/textslide-475x580.png 475w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/textslide.png 525w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 475px) 100vw, 475px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Once you are done with all the settings, click <strong>Apply</strong> to save the slide. You would be able to see the text slide into the slider.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-19213 size-large\" src=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/text-slide-preview-580x374.png\" alt=\"Text slide preview\" width=\"580\" height=\"374\" srcset=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/text-slide-preview-580x374.png 580w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/text-slide-preview.png 748w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 580px) 100vw, 580px\" /></a></p>\n<p><strong>Video Slide &#8211; </strong>To add a video slide, <em>Click</em> <strong>Add Slide </strong>button&nbsp;and choose <strong>Video Slide</strong>. A lightbox will appear where you have the options to add <strong>Youtube, DailyMotion, </strong>and<strong> Vimeo Video </strong>and also<strong> HTML5 videos.</strong></p>\n<p>Simply add the URL of the video and click <strong>Apply </strong>to save the slide.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-19209 size-large\" src=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/video-580x554.png\" alt=\"Video slider\" width=\"580\" height=\"554\" srcset=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/video-580x554.png 580w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/video.png 685w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 580px) 100vw, 580px\" /></a></p>\n<p><strong>HTML Slide &#8211; </strong>To add an HTML slide, <em>Click</em> <strong>Add Slide</strong> Button and choose <strong>HTML Slide</strong>. A&nbsp;lightbox will appear where you can put any HTML code. It can be an image, map, text, video, etc.Once you are done, click <strong>Apply</strong> to save.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-19214 size-large\" src=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/html-580x450.png\" alt=\"HTML slider\" width=\"580\" height=\"450\" srcset=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/html-580x450.png 580w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/html-768x596.png 768w, https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/html.png 771w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 580px) 100vw, 580px\" /></a></p>\n<h4>STEP Three: Save Slider</h4>\n<p>Click <strong>Save SlideDeck </strong>button&nbsp;to save all the settings.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-18878 size-full\" src=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Save_Slidedeck.png\" alt=\"Save SlideDeck\" width=\"124\" height=\"33\"/></a></p>\n<h4>STEP Four: Add the slider to your WordPress site</h4>\n<p>Finally, it is time&nbsp;to&nbsp;add your slider to a post or page. Select any of three available ways to publish the slider on your site.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-18928 size-full\" src=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/publish-methods.png\" alt=\"Publish your SlideDeck\" width=\"466\" height=\"486\"/></a></p>\n<p>By the end of this tutorial, you will have a full-width <a href=\"http://www.slidedeck.com/docs/#mix-slide-type\" target=\"_blank\">mixed slider</a> that looks like this.</p>\n<div class=\"slidedeck-link\"><a href=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/mixed-content-slider-wordpress/#SlideDeck-19225\">Mixed Content Slider <small>[see the SlideDeck]</small></a></div>\n<p>Hope this tutorial helped you setting up the slider with mix content on your site.</p>\n<p>Check out our other tutorial on creating a <a href=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/zenfolio-gallery-slider-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\">Zenfolio slider in WordPress</a>.</p>\n<p>If you have any feedback or questions, please let me know in the comments.</p>\n<br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.slidedeck.com/pricing/?utm_source=feed_ad&utm_medium=banner&utm_campaign=sd_blog\"><img src=\"//s3.amazonaws.com/assets-slidedeck2/wp-content/themes/slidedeck2/images/sd-rss.jpg\" alt=\"Easily create AWESOME WordPress sliders - Get SlideDeck\" style=\"display:block;border:none;\"/></a><p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.slidedeck.com/mixed-content-slider-wordpress/\">How to create a Mixed Content Slider in WordPress?</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.slidedeck.com\">Responsive WordPress Slider Plugin</a>.</p>\n<div class=\"feedflare\">\n<a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a=Xp_WhAM0Zak:z3IxlowEk7s:yIl2AUoC8zA\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?d=yIl2AUoC8zA\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a=Xp_WhAM0Zak:z3IxlowEk7s:gIN9vFwOqvQ\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?i=Xp_WhAM0Zak:z3IxlowEk7s:gIN9vFwOqvQ\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a=Xp_WhAM0Zak:z3IxlowEk7s:V_sGLiPBpWU\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?i=Xp_WhAM0Zak:z3IxlowEk7s:V_sGLiPBpWU\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a=Xp_WhAM0Zak:z3IxlowEk7s:qj6IDK7rITs\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?d=qj6IDK7rITs\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?a=Xp_WhAM0Zak:z3IxlowEk7s:F7zBnMyn0Lo\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Slidedeck?i=Xp_WhAM0Zak:z3IxlowEk7s:F7zBnMyn0Lo\" border=\"0\"></img></a>\n</div><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/Slidedeck/~4/Xp_WhAM0Zak\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0